--- !u!114 &1364323518
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1364323516}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "The first theme I noticed in the feedback was related to the cameras,
    mainly that the cameras were too consistent. More specifically, the FoV is consistent
    between the cameras, and that I should make the wide shots wider, the close-up
    more zoomed in, and that more should be done with the follow camera beyond it
    following directly behind the character, such as an over-the-shoulder view. The
    camera that rotates around the peak should also rotate for a longer period of
    time. One person also gave feedback that I should include a first-person view,
    and another that I need to pace my shots better as they are a little fast.\r\n\r\nThis
    feedback matters because a large part of the game that I\u2019m basing my cutscene
    off of is how beautiful the game is. Therefore, I should use the cameras to show
    off my scene more.\n\nThe second theme is related to the environment and its
    lack of detail. Feedback included that I  should add some voronoi noise to the
    water to make it stand out more, add some decor to the scene, sharpen the fog
    a little, and texture the mountain. I also received the feedback that I should
    add a Smooth Step node to my aurora shader so that it does not cut-off as abruptly,
    and that the snow particles are under-developed.\r\n\r\nThis feedback matters
    because, like the previous theme, the original game likes to focus on the view,
    so it\u2019s important to add a view to look at. Also, not having textures would
    severely reduce my grade for the final submission.\r\n\r\n"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
